As a Solutions Analyst at ALDI, you will be helping to lead and support a brand new Information Governance Program. The Solutions Analyst reports to the IT Manager and is responsible for managing projects supporting Information Governance and implementing program components (program policies and standards, retention schedule, communications to employees, education and training, compliance and program assessment). The ideal candidate for this role will be a self-starter, team player, and is able to lead projects working across functional teams. As ALDI reviews and improves its information governance standards fostering a compliance culture, you will be responsible for the governance of electronic records, including monitoring of compliance with information governance policies and assisting with data classification and information sharing practices. Understanding the value of data, as well the policies that support data usage and data repositories, the ideal candidate will need to have experience developing and improving methods of compliance monitoring. It will be necessary for the chosen candidate to have experience creating retention schedules, and ensuring all Governance standards are met, meeting best in class policy standards. As this role will be visible to all business partners, and/or leaders, we are looking for someone that has excellent communication skills (verbal and written), with the ability to present to and train diversely skilled audiences. As a Solutions Analyst at ALDI supporting information governance, your input, ideas, recommendations, evaluations and improvements will be valued.

JOB SUMMARY
This job supports one or more analytical aspects of the application product life cycle, including capability enablement with cross-team dependencies within a product scope. Requires expert level of understanding the end systems impact of changes across enterprise-wide systems (including regulatory risk exposure, customer service & financial impacts).

Equivalent Experience
Description:
We have an opening in Clearfield, UT for a Hybrid opportunity as a mid-sr. Cyber Security Information Analyst. This person must hold a current CISSP certification, or equivalent to any IAM-II Certification: (CAP, CASP+ CE, CISM, GSLC, CCISO). *Candidates must be willing to commute, or re-locate to Clearfield, UT.*
This person will perform technical oversight and direction in the following tasks: Assessments of systems and networks within the networking environment or enclave and identify where those systems and networks deviate from acceptable configurations, enclave policy, or local policy. This is achieved through passive evaluations such as compliance audits and active evaluations such as vulnerability assessments. Establishes strict program control processes to ensure mitigation of risks and supports obtaining certification and accreditation of systems. Includes support of process, analysis, coordination, security certification test, security documentation, as well as investigations, software research, hardware introduction and release, emerging technology research inspections and periodic audits. Assist in the implementation of the required government policy, make recommendations on process tailoring, participate in and document process activities. Perform analyses to validate established security requirements and to recommend additional security requirements and safeguards. Support the formal Security Test and Evaluation (ST&E) required by each government accrediting authority through pre-test preparations, participation in the tests, analysis of the results and preparation of required reports. Document the results of Certification and Accreditation activities and technical or coordination activity and prepare the system Security Plans and update the Plan of Actions and Milestones POA&M. Periodically conduct a complete review of each system's audits and monitor corrective actions until all actions are closed.

Position Description:
A Cyber Security Analyst is responsible for providing various cybersecurity consulting services for reseller partners / to end clients. Consulting services include, but are limited to, Penetration Testing and Vulnerability Assessments.

Essence of the Position:
The purpose, the meaning, the essence of the Cybersecurity Analyst role has two distinct attributes. The first is is to educate end clients about their unique risks and the second is to help reseller partners understand how to mitigate those risks.
Cybersecurity remains an abstract concept to most of our clients and reseller partners. The Cybersecurity Analyst has a parental like responsibility to explain technical information to a non-technical audience and provide clear and simple instructions to improve.




Mandatory Certification

Title: Products & Services System Analyst
Job_Description:
Equivalent Experience
Description:
Summary:
The Vulnerability Operations team is a governance team aligned to the Technology Infrastructure and Information Security organizations. The team provides oversight of outstanding enterprise-wide software vulnerabilities and facilitates their rapid research and subsequent closure. The team also owns the policy and regulatory controls surrounding delivery of this service for the company.
Vulnerability remediation demands are communicated to relevant CIO-owned, in-scope teams which execute the work in their specific silos. Because they are focused on their responsibilities and actions, individual application/product teams digest and act on the demand independently of other teams. Any challenges or escalations are done on a team by team basis with little to no ability to share best practices or concerns across the affected teams unless the initiative does so proactively. There are significant efficiency and cost savings opportunities in finding ways to improve information sharing across the in-scope teams and in automating and/or streamlining relevant improvements and guidance for the teams this group leads and supports. Similarly this role can observe challenges to getting the work done and proactively engage necessary parties before an escalation to senior leadership is needed, mitigating noise and churn for already busy teams and leaders.

Title: Products & Services System Analyst

This resource will maintain legal and regulatory compliance by researching and communicating requirements and obtaining approvals. This includes a primary role in regulatory audit activities, including but not limited to Sorbanes-Oxley (SOX) and Payment Card Industry (PCI) audits. The IT Compliance Analyst will coordinate with Internal Audit team members as well as external auditors to gather and submit evidence, maintain communications during audits, and interface with IT team management. Outside of audit activities, the IT Compliance Analyst will have other responsibilities related to legal and regulatory compliance, including but not limited to legal contract review, updates to IT policies and procedures, and recurring security training and reviews.
Qualifications:
Excellent communication, interpersonal, and organization skills. 3-5 years of experience in a related field (such as law or audit). Exceptional ability to formulate compliance policies, procedures, and related documentation. Advanced analytical abilities and exceptional attention to detail. Ability to accurately complete applications for compliance certification.

Title: Assistant Superintendent
Job_Description:
The CPC is primarily responsible for front-end processing of Freedom of Information Act (FOIA), Privacy Act (PA), Mandatory Declassification Review (MDR) Requests, Appeals, And other Requests that involve declassification actions – EEO, Administrative Actions, Incident Reports, Litigation Cases, External Referrals, Foreign Relations of the United State {FRUS} and Other cases. The number one responsibility is to insure that new Requests are entered into the Automated Document Review System using the Software interface, that a new Case number Is generated, and that all correspondence an documents associated with each Case be properly Scanned and indexed. In addition, CPC members are responsible for checking the unclassified Computer and the unclassified faxTerminal (Housed in the CPC spaces) on a daily basis for new Requests, Appeals letters, or follow-on correspondence associated with existing Cases. The CPC also serves as the delivery and transmittal center for all government Executive Order (E.O.) Referrals to other U.S. government agencies, and for client responses to MDR, FRUS, and other Special Topic Cases. The CPC team leader is responsible for personnel issues within the CPC (i.e., planning sufficient Man-hour distribution, overseeing training needs, and making sure that all computer and security Accesses are obtained as needed). Other responsibilities include interaction with the government and Contract program manager on all issues affecting the proper functioning of the CPC, and providing Weekly statistical reports on activities completed. Given the multitude of tasks in the CPC, and the part-time work schedules of the CPC workforce, it is Imperative that all members be able to perform all required tasks. Attention to detail is also mandatory For this position. Interaction with other components requires a friendly, can-do attitude. With the Variety of responsibilities and functions in the CPC, the work is never boring.

To protect the health and safety of its employees and to comply with customer requirements, PTFS will require all employees to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19.. Vaccination requirements will depend on the status of the federal contractor mandate and customer site requirements.

Job_Description:
Gallagher Bassett (GB) is a for-profit company with a positive social impact. We help injured workers get back to health (and back to work) faster, cheaper, and with less administrative burden. In broader terms, we're a company of experts navigating the complex world of claims management so that our clients can focus on their own businesses.
